item.description:
to install .sh files  make the file executable: Here we have two options: a) right click over the file, go to properties, then click on the Permissions tab and then in Execute, check the &lsquo;Allow executing file as program&rsquo; option. b) In the terminal write this command line :bash:&lsquo;chmod ug+x ./file_name.sh&rsquo;
 execute the file in the terminal using the command line, :bash:&lsquo;./file_name.sh&rsquo;
  install a .deb file  execute in the terminal using the command line, :bash:&lsquo;sudo dpkg -i filename.

